# User Interview Notes — Session 3
**Date:** June 14, 2025
**Participant:** Diana, Engineering Manager, 6 months using the product
**Interviewer:** Ali

---

## Opening

**Q: How do you use the product in your role as an engineering manager?**

"I use it to track what my team is working on, mostly. I check in maybe 3 times a week."

**Q: What does a typical check-in look like?**

"I log in, try to get a sense of what's in progress, what's blocked, what was completed recently. It takes longer than it should."

---

## Pain Points

**Q: What's the hardest part about getting that overview?**

"There's no single view that shows me my whole team. I have to go into each person's profile or each project separately. It's very click-heavy."

"I want to see: who's working on what, what's overdue, what got done this week. In one place. That doesn't exist."

**Q: Does this affect how often you log in?**

"Definitely. If I know it's going to take 10 minutes to piece together a picture, I'll postpone it. I probably check in less than I should because of that friction."

---

## Current Workarounds

**Q: How do you currently solve for this?**

"I have a weekly standup where everyone updates me verbally. The tool should be able to replace that, but it can't yet."

"I also send a Slack message on Fridays asking for status updates. Manual process."

---

## Feature Requests

**Q: What would make you a daily user?**

"A team digest. Show me what changed since I last logged in. Bullet points. Who moved what, what got completed, what's newly blocked. Email it to me every morning or let me pull it up in one click."

"If I could get that in under 60 seconds I'd be in here every single day."
